The paper deals with the complexity of computing the sign of the Tutte polynomial, which is a well-studied topic in computational complexity theory. The paper uses techniques from computational complexity theory, graph theory, and algebraic combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
